This paper deals with the problem of routing a data packet through a polygonal domain, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents a routing scheme that achieves a path whose length is within a factor of $1+\varepsilon$ of the shortest path, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and simulation (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves some combinatorial aspects, such as labeling and routing tables, which could fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
